						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarmaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tribhº Vīra-chōḷadēva: Year 21 = 1202-04 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription<note n="103-1">The two other items included along with this in <hi rend="italic">A.R.S.I.E.,</hi> 1909, are missing.</note>is incomplete. It refers to the king as one who ruled the two Koggu together, and records a gift of land, made by the king, to provide for offerings to the god of VīrachōḻIśvaramuḍaiyār who was set up and consecrated in Koḻumam for the merit of the king.</p>						

